{"created": "2025-12-09T06:06:43.968958+00:00", "modified": "2025-12-09T06:06:44.578040+00:00", "id": 17862831, "conceptrecid": "17862830", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.17862831", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.17862830", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17862831", "metadata": {"title": "Recursive Entropy Calculus: Bounds and Resonance in Hierarchically Partitioned Systems", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.17862831", "publication_date": "2025-12-09", "description": "<p>We develop Recursive Entropy Calculus (REC), a rigorous mathematical framework&nbsp;extending Shannon information entropy to hierarchically partitioned probability spaces.&nbsp;Classical entropy theory provides static measures at fixed scales; REC introduces a depth-&nbsp;indexed calculus that tracks entropy evolution S(d) across recursive subdivision levels d.&nbsp;We establish four fundamental theorems: (A) the Entropic Ceiling &macr;S(d) &le; 1, (B) the&nbsp;Growth Ceiling &tilde;r(d) &le; 2, (C) Asymptotic Convergence &tilde;r(d) &rarr; 1, and (D) the Geometric&nbsp;Bound &zeta; = dH/D &le; 1 for volume-convergent recursive geometries. All bounds are proven<br>from first principles with complete proofs provided.&nbsp;We distinguish these proven results from the empirically observed 5:4 wave resonance&nbsp;ratio (Reid Constant R = 5/4), which applies to physical wave systems in recursive cavities and requires further theoretical development. Comprehensive computational validation,&nbsp;illustrative examples, and reproducible code confirm all theoretical predictions. The framework provides new tools for analyzing hierarchical data structures, fractal thermodynamics,<br>and multi-scale information systems.</p>", "access_right": "open", "creators": [{"name": "Reid, Steven", "affiliation": null, "orcid": "0009-0003-9132-3410"}], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "10.5281/ZENODO.17690619", "relation": "isPartOf", "resource_type": "publication-preprint", "scheme": "doi"}], "resource_type": {"title": "Preprint", "type": "publication", "subtype": "preprint"}, "license": {"id": "cc-by-4.0"}, "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type": "recid", "pid_value": "17862830"}}]}}, "title": "Recursive Entropy Calculus: Bounds and Resonance in Hierarchically Partitioned Systems", "links": {"self": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17862831", "self_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/17862831", "preview_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/17862831?preview=1", "doi": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17862831", "self_doi": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17862831", "self_doi_html": "https://zenodo.org/doi/10.5281/zenodo.17862831", "reserve_doi": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17862831/draft/pids/doi", "parent": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17862830", "parent_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/17862830", "parent_doi": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17862830", "parent_doi_html": "https://zenodo.org/doi/10.5281/zenodo.17862830", "self_iiif_manifest": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17862831/manifest", "self_iiif_sequence": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17862831/sequence/default", "files": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17862831/files", "media_files": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/17862831/media-files", "thumbnails": {"10": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17862831:Recursive_Entropy_Calculus__Bounds_and_Resonance_in_Hierarchically_Partitioned_Systems.pdf/full/%5E10,/0/default.jpg", "50": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17862831:Recursive_Entropy_Calculus__Bounds_and_Resonance_in_Hierarchically_Partitioned_Systems.pdf/full/%5E50,/0/default.jpg", "100": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17862831:Recursive_Entropy_Calculus__Bounds_and_Resonance_in_Hierarchically_Partitioned_Systems.pdf/full/%5E100,/0/default.jpg", "250": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:17862831:Recursive_Entropy_Calculus__Bounds_and_Resonance_in_Hierarchically_Partitioned_Systems.pdf/full/%5E250,/0/default.jpg", "750": "https://zenodo.org/api/iiif/record:1786283